      • setRequiresLogin

        public void setRequiresLogin(boolean requiresLogin)
        By default the SDK requires your users to log in, so the onboarding experience will be presented each time they launch the app until they either sign up or log in. If your app does not require users to have an account, you can turn this off, thus only showing the Primer experience once, the first time the app is installed and launched. You can configure this with the PrimerOptions class that you use when you initialize Primer.
        Parameters:
        requiresLogin - - whether or your app requires login.
